/// section bg:dark text:light
h2: Dark background
p: Use text:light when you need an explicit contrast override, such as for dark or custom-colored backgrounds.

/// section bg:muted
h2: Muted background
p: Uses Bootstrap's secondary background variable — a subtle surface tint that respects both light and dark themes.

/// section bg:success
h2: Bootstrap semantic — success
p: Bootstrap semantic tokens (success, warning, info, danger, dark, light) work without defining any brand colors.

